OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FTemperature hits 34.8C on  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FScotland's hottest day     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Scotland is experiencing its hottest   
OL,6, day ever, after a temperature of 34.8C 
OL,7, (94.6F) was recorded in the Borders.   
OL,9,FThe Met Office confirmed Charterhall   
OL,10,Fhad provisionally set the new record on
OL,11,FTuesday.                               
OL,13,FIt surpasses the previous record of    
OL,14,F32.9C recorded in Greycrook in the     
OL,15,FBorders on 9 August 2003.              
OL,17,FIt comes on day two of an amber weather
OL,18,Fwarning for extreme heat and just hours
OL,19,Fafter the UK set a new record of 40.2C 
OL,20,Fat Heathrow in London.                 
